			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The debug stub's main loop currently works by polling 10 times per second to wait for something to do.  See the &amp;quot;IPlatform::Relinquish(100)&amp;quot; call in target.cc.

We can make the debug stub a lot more responsive if we remove this busy-waiting and do things properly.

This will need to wait until after issue 2948 is addressed, since that will overhaul how the debug stub gets notified about untrusted faults.
